race.comment: BOUTIQUE BELLE (9) may have only run ninth on debut but the effort was full of merit. Drew off the track and went back to the tail but made good ground late in a tougher race than this. Better for the experience and expected to feature. APACHE ADIOS (6) crossed and led fresh, giving a sight before finishing fifth. Tried to do the same last time and finished fifth again over 1000m. Has better form over the 1200m and expected to lead and give a sight. SHEZASEER (7) wasn't far away over 1200m fresh then stepped to 1400m and was back and wide and finished midfield. Back in trip and will find this easier so worth another try. TAKE A LEAF (11) is on debut. By Long Leaf and hails from the Tom Wolfe stable. Placed at her most recent trial and aided by the claim. Worth watching for a betting push. MAGIC CARATS (3) resumes and wasn't too far away when last fresh-up. Worth including.
